punch first and
ask questions later.

33
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:38,583
Well, it looked
really bad!

34
00:03:40,083 --> 00:03:41,458
Sorry.

35
00:03:44,875 --> 00:03:47,208
As far as she's
concerned...

36
00:03:47,291 --> 00:03:50,041
She really
puts it away.

37
00:03:50,125 --> 00:03:52,083
No kidding!

38
00:03:52,166 --> 00:03:54,916
[YUKINARI] Miharu accidentally
came to Earth not too long ago,

39
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:57,000
from her home planet, Seiren,

40
00:03:57,083 --> 00:04:01,125
a world filled almost
totally with women.

41
00:04:03,333 --> 00:04:05,333
Since then, we've tried
sending her back

42
00:04:05,416 --> 00:04:06,958
a bunch of different ways,

43
00:04:07,041 --> 00:04:09,291
but no luck so far.

44
00:04:09,375 --> 00:04:12,958
For now, at least,
she's staying at my house.

45
00:04:13,041 --> 00:04:14,125
[MIHARU]
Yukinari!

46
00:04:14,208 --> 00:04:15,500
Huh?

47
00:04:15,583 --> 00:04:18,500
This is really tasty!
I was wondering what it is.

48
00:04:18,583 --> 00:04:19,791
[KIRIE]
The thin pieces?

49
00:04:19,875 --> 00:04:21,666
They're called bread.

50
00:04:21,750 --> 00:04:22,833
Do you like it?

51
00:04:22,916 --> 00:04:24,750
Yeah!

52
00:04:24,833 --> 00:04:28,416
Kirie understands the...
unique situation with Miharu.

53
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:30,750
So they don't have any bread
on the planet that you're from?

54
00:04:30,833 --> 00:04:32,166
Now she actually
helps me out with her.

55
00:04:32,250 --> 00:04:33,375
Nuh-uh, but we do have

56
00:04:33,458 --> 00:04:35,666
a similar kind of food
that we call "pana."

57
00:04:35,750 --> 00:04:38,333
For her part, Miharu doesn't
seem too homesick for Seiren...

58
00:04:38,416 --> 00:04:39,833
"Pana"?

59
00:04:39,916 --> 00:04:41,083
...which is good, because we
don't know how to get her there.

60
00:04:41,166 --> 00:04:42,833
I guess that's
a good thing.

61
00:04:42,916 --> 00:04:43,916
Yukinari!

62
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:46,708
Thank you!
That food is wonderful!

63
00:04:46,791 --> 00:04:50,583
It's so soft and tasty.

64
00:04:50,666 --> 00:04:51,916
