86
00:05:44,291 --> 00:05:46,833
Well, it's not
that I can't.

87
00:05:46,916 --> 00:05:49,916
But the school curry bread
is the most popular one!

88
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:52,708
And it sells out when
the lunch bell rings!

89
00:05:52,791 --> 00:05:54,208
Kirie said so!

90
00:05:54,291 --> 00:05:55,375
Yeah, but I--

91
00:05:55,458 --> 00:05:56,708
Yukinari, come on.

92
00:05:56,791 --> 00:05:59,125
We're gonna miss first period
if we don't get going.

93
00:05:59,208 --> 00:06:00,916
Oh, right.

94
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:03,333
Sorry, Miharu,
we have to go,

95
00:06:03,416 --> 00:06:04,541
but don't you worry!

96
00:06:04,625 --> 00:06:07,791
I'll get that
curry bread for you.

97
00:06:08,458 --> 00:06:10,375
Oh yeah, there are
snacks in the cupboard.

98
00:06:10,458 --> 00:06:12,666
Help yourself
if you get hungry.

99
00:06:12,750 --> 00:06:14,541
I'll see you later.

100
00:06:29,416 --> 00:06:31,833
I'm so hungry.

101
00:06:33,083 --> 00:06:37,500
Bread. School bread.

102
00:06:38,166 --> 00:06:39,666
It must be like silk.

103
00:06:39,750 --> 00:06:43,541
Spicy curry wrapped inside
all that doughy goodness.

104
00:06:43,625 --> 00:06:46,458
With one bite,
it fills the mouth

105
00:06:46,541 --> 00:06:51,583
with warmth and
leaves you ecstatic!

106
00:06:51,666 --> 00:06:53,458
I want it.

107
00:06:56,458 --> 00:06:58,958
That's it!

108
00:06:59,041 --> 00:07:01,083
If I buy the school
bread for myself,

109
00:07:01,166 --> 00:07:03,583
I don't have to
wait for Yukinari,

110
00:07:03,666 --> 00:07:06,458
and that means
I get to go outside.

111
00:07:06,541 --> 00:07:09,250
I'm outside on
a beautiful day!

112
00:07:12,291 --> 00:07:15,583
Hmm, I wonder how
I get to Yukinari's school.

113
00:07:49,125 --> 00:07:52,958
Ah! Hello, hello!
Bananas are on sale, today!

114
00:07:53,041 --> 00:07:56,083
Want some, lady?
No? How 'bout you?

115
00:07:57,500 --> 00:07:59,458
[VENDOR sighs]

116
00:08:02,458 --> 00:08:03,833
Huh?

117
00:08:04,833 --> 00:08:07,958
Oh, Miss, can I help
you with something?

118
00:08:08,041 --> 00:08:12,000
Are these okay to eat?
They smell really good.

119
00:08:12,083 --> 00:08:15,666
Uh, you've never
seen a banana before?

120
00:08:15,750 --> 00:08:17,291
It's a banana?

121
00:08:17,375 --> 00:08:18,375
It's a banana.

122
00:08:18,458 --> 00:08:20,125
So, it's a banana.

123
00:08:20,208 --> 00:08:21,125
Yeah, it's
a banana.

124
00:08:21,208 --> 00:08:23,000
Is it different
than curry bread?

125
00:08:23,083 --> 00:08:25,041
It is very different
than curry bread.

126
00:08:26,125 --> 00:08:27,958
That's what I thought.

127
00:08:29,625 --> 00:08:31,625
Yeah, they're
the sale item for today.

128
00:08:31,708 --> 00:08:34,708
Are they going
to sell out?

129
00:08:35,583 --> 00:08:38,541
Well, the demand for
bananas has been down lately.

130
00:08:38,625 --> 00:08:41,000
People just don't eat 'em
as much as they used to.

131
00:08:41,083 --> 00:08:42,333
Oh, I'm sorry.

132
00:08:42,416 --> 00:08:43,958
Yeah, in the old days,

133
00:08:44,041 --> 00:08:45,916
bananas were
a pretty ritzy fruit...

134
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,333
really hard to come by.

135
00:08:47,416 --> 00:08:49,833
Imported fruit!
Fit for a king!

136
00:08:49,916 --> 00:08:53,250
Wow, fit for a king!
That's really incredible.

137
00:08:53,333 --> 00:08:55,208
[VENDOR laughs]
Wanna try one?

138
00:08:55,291 --> 00:08:56,375
Is it okay?

139
00:08:56,458 --> 00:08:57,833
Sure.

140
00:08:59,333 --> 00:09:00,916
Dig in.

141
00:09:28,291 --> 00:09:29,083
You like it?

142
00:09:29,166 --> 00:09:31,708
Yes! Thank you,
it's good!

143
00:09:31,791 --> 00:09:33,208
It's really
soft and very sweet!

144
00:09:33,291 --> 00:09:35,416
It is, isn't it?

145
00:09:35,500 --> 00:09:40,708
I can remember the very first
banana that I ever tasted.

146
00:09:40,791 --> 00:09:43,125
Heh, changed my life forever.

147
00:09:43,208 --> 00:09:44,916
I was a boy of fifteen.

148
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:47,458
I was in bed with
a bad case of the measles,

149
00:09:47,541 --> 00:09:49,583
and my mother,
poor woman that she was,

150
00:09:49,666 --> 00:09:52,208
went without to buy me bananas.

151
00:09:52,291 --> 00:09:55,166
She fed me those bananas
with her own chapped hands

152
00:09:55,250 --> 00:09:58,166
with such devotion it
made me want to weep

153
00:09:58,250 --> 00:10:00,583
tears of gratitude flowed down
my young face like a river,

154
00:10:00,666 --> 00:10:03,458
as I kept saying,
"It's good. It's good."

155
00:10:06,083 --> 00:10:08,625
There and then, I vowed
that I would someday

156
00:10:08,708 --> 00:10:10,666
open my own
produce store.

157
00:10:10,750 --> 00:10:13,791
Taiwan, China,
the Philippines, Ecuador!

158
00:10:13,875 --> 00:10:16,500
I sailed the world over
chasing a dream.

159
00:10:16,583 --> 00:10:19,291
I can remember how many
times I almost perished at sea,

160
00:10:19,375 --> 00:10:23,250
but it was all worth it when
I finally found the very best

161
00:10:23,333 --> 00:10:26,291
bananas and brought them back!

162
00:10:27,833 --> 00:10:31,166
I negotiated the planters
into an exclusive contract!

163
00:10:31,250 --> 00:10:33,333
The first shipment
sold in minutes.

164
00:10:33,416 --> 00:10:35,750
I spent every
penny on this building,

165
00:10:35,833 --> 00:10:39,166
and now, by God,
I sell bananas!

166
00:10:46,041 --> 00:10:48,625
I see, the day-to-day
grind made me forget

167
00:10:48,708 --> 00:10:52,666
why I wanted into the produce
business in the first place.

168
00:10:52,750 --> 00:10:54,833
That brush with destiny...

169
00:10:54,916 --> 00:10:57,625
Thanks for the banana.
It was good for me, too.

170
00:10:57,708 --> 00:11:00,000
Ah, it was nothing
at all, young lady.

171
00:11:00,083 --> 00:11:01,916
If anything,
I should thank you.

172
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:06,208
Oh, um... do you know
anything about school bread?

173
00:11:06,291 --> 00:11:08,666
I've been looking
for some all morning now.

174
00:11:08,750 --> 00:11:10,250
Bread?

175
00:11:10,333 --> 00:11:12,833
Yukinari told me
they sell it as his school.

176
00:11:12,916 --> 00:11:16,041
At his school?
You mean Mizuno High School?

177
00:11:16,125 --> 00:11:17,708
If that's where you mean,

178
00:11:17,791 --> 00:11:20,041
go straight, turn right,
and it'll be right there.

179
00:11:20,125 --> 00:11:23,041
Thank you very much.
See you later!

180
00:11:23,125 --> 00:11:23,875
Sure! Come again,
anytime.

181
00:11:23,958 --> 00:11:27,875
See you around,
banana girl!

182
00:11:27,958 --> 00:11:28,958
Huh?

183
00:11:29,041 --> 00:11:31,000
This smells good,
what's it called?

184
00:11:31,083 --> 00:11:33,083
It's called a croquette.

185
00:11:33,166 --> 00:11:35,541
They must have broke
the mold after that one.

186
00:11:37,166 --> 00:11:38,875
